[2]
Date: Sat 11 May 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Agencia EFE, Sat 11 May 2002 [edited]

Costa Rica: Concern at High number of Dengue Fever Cases
--------------------------------------------------------
SAN JOSE: The Costa Rican Health Minister warned of the possible [begining]
of an epidemic of dengue fever in the country's Pacific coastal area, where
1230 cases of the disease have been reported this year. Health Minister
Maria del Rocio Saenz said that her concern was based on the relatively
high number of cases registered prior to this month's onset of the rainy
season, when breeding conditions are more favorable for the _Aedes aegypti_
mosquito that transmits the disease.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
